BROW REFRESHER ! ! !

This client of mine had her brows originally done by another artist a few years back and was in need of having them refreshed. As they were previously microbladed she had a lot of scar tissue buildup - this means continuing to microblade them wouldn’t make sense for her as the color wouldn’t last that long in the tissue of the skin.

So in comes NANO BROWS!! This machine stroke technique is a great way to give her back her brows without continuing to damage her skin. ALSO, the color will last longer now that we can implement it into the skin using a machine stroke pixel method.

Any question?? List them below.

HEALED STROKES! ✨✨

Here are some beautifully healed #NanoBrows on my lovely friend and client @rachelgoodwinmakeup. These were done back in December and are still staying strong.

For clients with oily skin, as well as for those who love a good sweaty workout, Nano Brows are a GREAT option. They heal crisp and strong in the skin without the quick fading of microblading. Let me know what you think!!

YOU ASK, I ANSWER…

“How do I find the right brow artist for me?” 

This is a complex question because there’s some background that I think it’s important for any incoming client to understand. If you’re in the state of California, you can LITERALLY become a body art practitioner (that includes: tattoo artists, permanent makeup artists, body piercers and branders) in 24hrs. All it takes is filling out a form, a copy of a valid Drivers License/ID, a certificate of completion of Blood Borne Pathogens test (this takes 4hrs), 1 passport photo, and a check for $54. EASY. There is no required apprenticeship (which I personally think is the real key to all of this, or just plain tenacity), but you can open a practice overnight after getting the proper permitting.

My point in all this is to do your due diligence. I’ve seen so much poor work out there that I just want to help educate clientele so they can make the right decisions from the get go. 

Ask me your questions! I’m here to help.

Here is a quick breakdown of my #sixsimplerules. I hope this answers a lot of your questions. If it doesn't-don't be shy- ask me, I want to help you. And, so fun I had an unexpected guest, the lovely @michalmakeup. Please enjoy.
